Puzzle


&nbsp;


I know, I know. It&rsquo;s just the look I have. Puzzled. So that&rsquo;s my name Puzzle.&nbsp; But it&rsquo;s okay, because I&rsquo;m so much happier indoors with my brother, Whisp, than out there in the cold alleys. I&rsquo;ll take the name Puzzle if it means I get to eat snacks and sleep in that amazing cat hammock...Wait...Hold on...did somebody say snacks?&nbsp; I&rsquo;m sure I heard a snack bag shaking just now. Oh wait, that was me. Sorry. I get a little side tracked when someone brings up snacks. Right, ok, so about me...well, my best friend is my brother, Whisp. We go everywhere together, so we gotta go into a happy home together. We are both pretty shy, and loud noises kinda scare me still.&nbsp; I haven&rsquo;t fully been able to shake of the life I lived before the warmth of the indoors,&nbsp; but I know that when that perfect comes for me and my brother, that person with have the love and patience needed to help us adjust and feel safe. We require a hammock to help in the transition, lots of toys...especially the laser pointer. I mean it&rsquo;s mandatory. Oh, and snacks, I have a favorite actually...licky treats. We just turned 1 year old this month of April 2019, and I was so happy to get licky treats! They are like gogurts for cats! Seriously. They are the best. I enjoy a human bed on occasion and to be next to human legs because hey are warm and...I&rsquo;m hearing that snack bag again. Do you hear that? You should come over hear and have a snack with me. BYOS! See you soon!

Whisp


&nbsp;


I&rsquo;m sleek, lean, and handsome. I&rsquo;ve got this beautiful undercoat of white beneath my black exterior which makes me not just your average tuxedo kitty. Whisps of inconspicuous white swirls within the black of me...hmmmm I thunk I just figured out why they call me Whisp! That&rsquo;s Cool. So, I am on the shier end of the spectrum, but I&rsquo;m a ham for belly rubs especially if you catch me while I&rsquo;m napping. My sister Puzzle is my bestie, so we come as a pair. We grew up on the rough streets of Long Beach alleys until our foster mom caught us and loved us enough for us to believe humans can be kind. We were pretty scared out there, so it takes us a while to adjust to new surroundings. We will do best in a home without kids or dogs or other cats mainly because we want all of your attention, and we will be more able to come out and shine if it&rsquo;s just the two of us taking over your bed. Now days where spend most of our time together in our special hammock we got as a present. We LOVE THAT THING! We also love the laser pointer, my sister is a laser pointer hog, but the thing is so elusive that she can&rsquo;t catch it either! We just had our first birthday, we were so excited to get birthday snacks ( snacks are my absolute favorite thing ever.) Hard to believe I was born in April of 2018 and it&rsquo;s already 2019. Time sure does fly. I can&rsquo;t wait for time to go by in a loving forever home with my sister...that sounds like a dream come true&nbsp;
❤️
. I wonder who will come to love us...could it be you?
